</h4>

<p>
    Quantitatively, a momentum-time graph can be derived from a velocity-time graph
    by multiplying the entire y-axis scale by the mass of an object.
    A velocity-time graph can be derived from a momentum time graph
    by dividing the entire y-axis scale by the mass of the object.
    This relationship extends directly from the definition for momentum:
    \( p = mv \).
</p>

